description: * Binary Search Trees A Binary Search Tree (BST) is a type of tree that does have some structure attached to it. In a BST, nodes are organized in a manner where all values that are smaller than the root are placed to the left, and all values that are larger than the root are placed to the right. * so this is binery search tree or balanced tree  ![link](./classes/image/BST1.png)
